        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Soften the {{onion}} and {{garlic}} in a little oil in a wide pan. Add the {{spinach}} and stir until wilted and the liquid has cooked away completely. Tip into a clean cloth and squeeze out all remaining moisture. Cool. Combine in a bowl with the crumbled {{feta}}, beaten {{eggs}}, a grating of {{nutmeg-whole}}, and the {{black-pepper}}. Do not add salt, the feta is salty.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Layer and bake, 35 to 40 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 190°C fan. Brush a 30 × 20 cm tin with melted {{unsalted-butter}}. Lay one sheet of {{filo-pastry}} in the tin, letting it overhang, and brush with butter. Layer five sheets this way, brushing each. Spread the filling evenly over the pastry. Top with the remaining five sheets, brushing each. Fold in the overhanging edges and brush the top. Score the surface into portions with a sharp knife, this makes it easier to cut cleanly when baked. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until deep golden and the layers are visibly separated and crisp. Rest for 10 minutes before cutting.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
